    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a mechanically sorted 2005 Porsche 911 Carrera. This 997.1 generation example features the 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six engine, delivering linear power through a precise 6-speed manual transaxle. The drivetrain is robust, with recent borescope inspections showing no signs of cylinder wall scoring and a verified IMS bearing upgrade for peace of mind. The chassis retains its signature communicative feedback, utilizing MacPherson struts and a multi-link rear setup that remains taut under lateral load. Braking performance is sharp, aided by four-piston monobloc calipers and fresh high-temp fluid. While the exterior displays minor stone chips consistent with spirited road use, the aerodynamic integrity and structural rigidity are excellent. This is a high-functioning driver's car that balances daily usability with track-ready engineering.",
